#Usage:
#------
video convert [files] [--format FORMAT] [--preset PRESET] [--resolution RES] [--framerate FPS]

#Description:
#------------
Convert videos into a selected format using ffmpeg.
Supports interactive mode if no parameters are given.

#Formats:
#--------
--format, -f        Target format: mp4 (default), mkv, webm, avi, mov, flv, mpeg
--preset, -p        Device presets:
                    messenger (super fast), web (fast), casual (balanced) (default), cinema (slow)
--resolution, -r    Target resolution: 240p, 360p, 480p, 720p, 1080p or original (default)
--framerate, -fr    Target FPS: 15 (Low quality), 23.976 (NTSC film), 24 (Cinema standard),
				29.97 (NTSC TV), 30 (Web/mobile), 50 (PAL HD),
				59.94 (NTSC HD), 60 (YouTube/Gaming), 120 (High FPS/Slow motion),
 				original (Use original framerate) (default)
--codec		    Target codec: libx264, libx265, vp9, mpeg4, copy (default)


#Examples:
#---------
video convert video1.avi --format mp4 --preset smartphone
video convert --format mkv --resolution 1080p --framerate 30

#Notes:
#------
- Input files will be searched in the current directory if not specified.
- Supports input: .mp4, .mkv, .avi, .mov, .flv, .webm
- Output is saved in the same directory with the new format extension.
